{"lemma":"دَخْلُ","slug":"دَخْلُ","root":"د.خ.ل","root_slug":"د-خ-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/د-خ-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دَخْلُ","root":"دخل","pos":"V","occurrence_count":76},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":22},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12246","n12247","n12253","n12254","n12255","n12256","n12257","n12272"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enter, go in, come in"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to penetrate, to pierce"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to befall, to seize, to come over (someone) (e.g. of a doubt, joy, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take up (a profession, etc.), to start"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to drop in on, to come to see, to call on, to visit"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to consummate a marriage, to cohabit, to sleep","examples":[{"text":"[…] مِنْ نِسَائِكُمُ اللَّاتِي دَخَلْتُمْ بِهِنَّ فَإِنْ لَمْ تَكُونُوا دَخَلْتُمْ بِهِنَّ فَلَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيْكُمْ […]","english":"[born] of the wives whom you have gone into—but if you have not gone into them there is no sin upon you"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to acquire"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to join, to convert to","examples":[{"text":"وَرَأَيْتَ ٱلنَّاسَ يَدْخُلُونَ فِي دِينِ ٱللّٰهِ أَفْوَاجًا","english":"and you see the people entering God's religion in throngs"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to participate in (something)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to belong to, to pertain to, to be included among"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be newly introduced [with عَلَى (ʕalā) ‘into something’] (e.g. of a factor, aspect, element, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be prefixed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to begin (of an event or occurrence)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be diseased, to be abnormal"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make enter, to bring in, to let in"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enter, to insert, to include"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"income"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"revenues, receipts, returns"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"interference, intervention"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"doubt, misgiving"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"disturbance, imbalance, derangement, disorder, mental defect"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"defect, infirmity"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/da.xa.la/","/dax.xa.la/","/daxl/","/da.xal/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12246","headword_ar":"دَخَلَ","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxuwlN","text_ar":"دُخُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madoxalN","text_ar":"مَدْخَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, entered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went, came, passed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"got, in; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraja","text_ar":"خَرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aid~axala","text_ar":"اِدَّخَلَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifotaEala","text_ar":"اِفْتَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Andxl","text_ar":"اندخل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) this last occuring in poetry, but not chaste, (S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tdx~l","text_ar":"تدخّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or this signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entered by little and little."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalotu madoxalFA HasanFA","text_ar":"دَخَلْتُ مَدْخَلًا حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxuwlFA HasanFA","text_ar":"دُخُولًا حَسَنًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I entered with a good entering"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalotu Albayota","text_ar":"دَخَلْتُ البَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra","text_ar":"الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I entered the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I became within the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like, (Msb,) correctly meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY Albayoti","text_ar":"اـِلَى البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c., or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Albayoti","text_ar":"فِى البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I entered into the house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], the prep. being suppressed, and the noun put in the accus. case after the manner of an objective complement: for nouns of place are of two kinds, vague and definite; the vague being such as the six relative locations,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalofN","text_ar":"خَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qud~aAmN","text_ar":"قُدَّامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamiynN","text_ar":"يَمِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imaAlN","text_ar":"شِمَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoqN","text_ar":"فَوْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHotN","text_ar":"تَحْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like, such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaAmN","text_ar":"اَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waraA='N","text_ar":"وَرَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaY","text_ar":"اَعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asofalu","text_ar":"اَسْفَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda","text_ar":"عِنْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laduno","text_ar":"لَدُنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasoTN","text_ar":"وَسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonN","text_ar":"بَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qubaAlapN","text_ar":"قُبَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", all which, and similar nouns of place, may become adverbs, because indefinite; for dost thou not see that what is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalof","text_ar":"خَلْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"to thee may be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qud~aAm","text_ar":"قُدَّام"},{"kind":"text","text":"to another? but that which is definite, having make, and corporeal substance, and tracts that comprehend it, as a mountain and a valley and a market and a house and a mosque, the noun signifying such a thing cannot become an adverb; for you may not say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEadotu Ald~aAra","text_ar":"قَعَدْتُ الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal~ayotu Almasojida","text_ar":"صَلَّيْتُ المَسْجِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nimotu Aljabala","text_ar":"نِمْتُ الجَبَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qumotu AlwaAdiYa","text_ar":"قُمْتُ الوَادِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the phrases of this kind that occur being instances of the suppression of a prep.; as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalotu Albayota","text_ar":"دَخَلْتُ البَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazalotu AlwaAdiYa","text_ar":"نَزَلْتُ الوَادِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEidotu Aljabala","text_ar":"صَعِدْتُ الجَبَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalotu EalaY zayodK Ald~aAra","text_ar":"دَخَلْتُ عَلَى زَيْدٍ الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I entered the house after Zeyd, he being in it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [And simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala Ealayohi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came in upon him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he came upon him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"invaded him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala biA@moraA^atihi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ بِا@مْرَاَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalayohaA","text_ar":"عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxuwlN","text_ar":"دُخُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala biA^aholihi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ بِاَهْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalayohaA","text_ar":"عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholN","text_ar":"اَهْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went in to his wife"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a metonymical phrase, denoting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljimaAE","text_ar":"الجِمَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwaTo'","text_ar":"الوَطْء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, TA,) whether it be such as is allowed by the law or such as is forbidden, (Mgh,) generally such as is lawful. (Msb, TA. [See what is said in explanation of the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalowapN","text_ar":"خَلْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlw","text_ar":"خلو"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala baEoDuhu fiY","text_ar":"دَخَلَ بَعْضُهُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoDK","text_ar":"بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadaAxala","text_ar":"تَدَاخَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSr","text_ar":"قصر"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) [For ex.,] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala baEoDu Aln~ujuwmi fiY baEoDK","text_ar":"دَخَلَ بَعْضُ النُّجُومِ فِى بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stars became confused together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$bk","text_ar":"شبك"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the former coupled with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AixotalaTato","text_ar":"اِخْتَلَطَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala fiyhimo","text_ar":"دَخَلَ فِيهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He entered among them, so as to become a member of their community, confraternity, party, sect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said of a stranger. (K.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala fiY TaAEatihi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ فِى طَاعَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^iEN","text_ar":"طَايِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TwE","text_ar":"طوع"},{"kind":"text","text":".] When"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala","text_ar":"دَخَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of income, or revenue, [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It came in, accrued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was received,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the aor. is as above, and the inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxolN","text_ar":"دَخْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadoxulu EalaY","text_ar":"يَدْخُلُ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_inosaAni","text_ar":"الاـِنْسَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It comes in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accrues, to the man"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb, K. *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala bihi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He entered with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: see 4. ―         -b2-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala fiyhi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became included, comprehended,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprised, in it."},{"kind":"text","text":"And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala fiY diyni AlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ فِى دِينِ الاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He entered within the pale of the religion of ElIslám; he entered the communion of that religion; he entered into, embraced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became a proselyte to, that religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"slm","text_ar":"سلم"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c. [See Kur cx. 2.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"دَخَلَ فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxuwlN","text_ar":"دُخُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He entered upon, began,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commenced, the affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala fiY A^amori gayorihi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ فِى اَمْرِ غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umuwri gayorihi","text_ar":"اُمُورِ غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tdx~l","text_ar":"تدخّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tdAxl","text_ar":"تداخل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He entered into,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mixed himself in, another's affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another's affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-  [Hence also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala Ealayohi","text_ar":"دَخَلَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of night, &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It came upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"invaded him."},{"kind":"text","text":"And said of a word, such as a prep. &c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, prefixed to it, preposed to it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put before it."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalaniY minohu","text_ar":"دَخَلَنِى مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems (from an instance in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bDE","text_ar":"بضع"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K) to mean (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An evil opinion of him entered my mind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxolN","text_ar":"دَخْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ a thing that induces doubt, or suspicion, or evil opinion. ”]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxila","text_ar":"دُخِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxila","text_ar":"دَخِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; inf. n. [of the former]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxolN","text_ar":"دَخْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of the latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalN","text_ar":"دَخَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had an unsoundness"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalN","text_ar":"دَخَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, K, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fasaAdN","text_ar":"فَسَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his intel-lect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his grounds of pretension to respect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in explanation of the former verb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxila A^amoruhu","text_ar":"دَخِلَ اَمْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalN","text_ar":"دَخَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, intrinsically bad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxila AlT~aEaAmu","text_ar":"دُخِلَ الطَّعَامُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The corn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food, became eaten by worms"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxila Ealayohi","text_ar":"دُخِلَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was led into a mistake,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an error, respecting a thing, without knowing it, by his having preconceived it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","K","MA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n12247","headword_ar":"دخّل","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadoxiylN","text_ar":"تَدْخِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put"},{"kind":"text","text":"dates"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dawoxal~ap","text_ar":"دَوْخَلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.) [In the present day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dx~lhu","text_ar":"دخّلهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the first of the senses assigned below to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoxalahu","text_ar":"اَدْخَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but for this I have not found any classical authority.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12253","headword_ar":"دَخْلٌ","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Income,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revenue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profit, that comes in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accrues, to a man from his immovable property, such as land and houses and palm-trees &c.,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and from his merchandise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarojN","text_ar":"خَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madoxuwlN","text_ar":"مَدْخُولٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madoxuwlN bihi","text_ar":"مَدْخُولٌ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) the former is originally an inf. n., of which the verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxala","text_ar":"دَخَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxoluhu A^akovaru mino xarojihi","text_ar":"دَخْلُهُ اَكْثَرُ مِنْ خَرْجِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His income is more than his outgoings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expenditure"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxolapN","text_ar":"دُخْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A disease;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalN","text_ar":"دَخَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA; but not decisively shown to have this meaning in the CK:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vice, fault, defect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blemish;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in one's grounds of pretension to respect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA,) as also, thus restricted, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalN","text_ar":"دَخَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that induces doubt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suspicion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil opinion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxalN","text_ar":"دَخَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. in all the senses explained in this sentence: each originally an inf. n.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxila","text_ar":"دُخِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxila","text_ar":"دَخِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) Hence the saying, (S, TA,) of"},{"kind":"text","text":"Athmeh Bint-Matrood, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamaA yudoriyka biAld~axoli \n                      \n                     \n                        taraY AlfitoyaAna kaAln~axoli"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou seest the youths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young men, like palmtrees; but what will acquaint thee with the vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., that is, or may be, in them]: (S, O, TA:) applied in relation to him who is of pleasing aspect, but devoid of good. (O, TA. [See also another reading of this verse voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqolapN","text_ar":"رَقْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dixaAlN","text_ar":"دِخَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A4-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxilN","text_ar":"دَخِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["T","Msb","K","TA","Az","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n12254","headword_ar":"دُخْلٌ","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of millet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAwarosN","text_ar":"جَاوَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxonN","text_ar":"دُخْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12255","headword_ar":"دِخْلٌ","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxolapN","text_ar":"دُخْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12256","headword_ar":"دَخَلٌ","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"primarily signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that enters into another thing and is not of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xvi. 94.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxolN","text_ar":"دَخْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Badness, corruptness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsoundness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bad, a corrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unsound, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dgl","text_ar":"دغل"},{"kind":"text","text":", and K;) in intellect or in body [&c.]. (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Eaqolihi daxalN","text_ar":"فِى عَقْلِهِ دَخَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his intellect is an unsoundness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aAAlA^amoru fiyhi daxalN","text_ar":"هٰذَاالاَمْرُ فِيهِ دَخَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dagalN","text_ar":"دَغَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, in it is an unsoundness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: both signify the same. (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rottenness"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a palm-tree. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leanness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perfidiousness, faithlessness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treachery:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K and TA; but not in the CK:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceit, guile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumvention."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) Hence, in the Kur [xvi. 96],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA tat~axi*uwA A^ayomaAnakumo daxalFA","text_ar":"وَلَا تَتَّخِذُوا اَيْمَانَكُمْ دَخَلًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonakumo","text_ar":"بَيْنَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And make ye not your oaths to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"a means of]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumvention, between you."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA. [And in the same sense it is used in verse 94 of the same ch.])       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"People,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons, who assert their relationship to those of whom they are not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) in this sense thought by ISd to be a quasi-pl. n. [app. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxiylN","text_ar":"دَخِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.), like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arafN","text_ar":"شَرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyfN","text_ar":"شَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo daxalN fiY baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"هُمْ دَخَلٌ فِى بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are, among the sons of such a one, persons who assert their relationship to them not being of them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [But Freytag asserts, though without naming any authority, evidently taking it from the TK, in which I find it, that one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hm dxl lhm","text_ar":"هم دخل لهم"},{"kind":"text","text":", and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hw","text_ar":"هو"},{"kind":"text","text":"; thus applying it to a single person (which is questionable) as well as to a plurality.] ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tangled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"luxuriant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant and dense, trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dagalN","text_ar":"دَغَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n12257","headword_ar":"دَخِلٌ","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intrinsically bad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsound:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxolN","text_ar":"دَخْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in the same sense at the end of a verse: this may be a contraction of the former, or it may be for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw daxolK","text_ar":"ذُو دَخْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12272","headword_ar":"دُخَّلٌ","root":"dxl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Herbage that enters among the stems of trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the lower parts of the branches of trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the branches of trees, and cannot be depastured by reason of its tangled state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euw~a*N","text_ar":"عُوَّذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feathers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions of feathers, that enter between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZuhoraAn","text_ar":"ظُهْرَان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTonaAn","text_ar":"بُطْنَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outermost and innermost portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) they are the best thereof, because the sun does not strike upon them. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions, of flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of muscle, lying within sinews:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh whereof one portion is intermixed with another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dux~alu All~aHomi","text_ar":"دُخَّلُ اللَّحْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flesh that cleaves to the bone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and such is the best of flesh. (T, TA.) ―         -b4-  Applied to a man, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thick, and compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contracted, in body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) lit,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having one portion thereof inserted into another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of small size,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust-coloured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that alights upon palm-trees and other trees, and enters among them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxolalN","text_ar":"دُخْلَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxolulN","text_ar":"دُخْلُلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dux~alapN","text_ar":"دُخَّلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ISd says that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an intrusive bird, smaller than the sparrow, found in El-Hijáz:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the T, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of small bird, like the sparrow, that has its abode in caves and in dense trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AHát says, in “the Book of Birds,” that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dux~alap","text_ar":"دُخَّلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bird that is found in caves, and enters houses"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tents, and is caught by children: when winter comes, the birds of this kind disperse; and some of them become of a dusky colour, and of a dark and somewhat reddish colour, and gray"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaroqaA='","text_ar":"زَرْقَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":");"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and some, variegated with blackness and redness, and with whiteness: they are of the size of the lark, but the latter is larger than they are in the head; neither short nor long in the tail; but short in the legs, which are like the legs of the lark:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxaAxiylu","text_ar":"دَخَاخِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) which is anomalous in respect of the insertion of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) in the T,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dxAlyl","text_ar":"دخاليل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is app. a mistranscription]. (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxolapN","text_ar":"دُخْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","M","TA"]}]}}